</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="312" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,258,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,474,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[446,600,474,499]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bermudezi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[446,600,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">N. bermudezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[611,704,474,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[611,704,474,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[932,1026,476,499]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="croix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[932,1026,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">N. croix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1036,1130,474,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1036,1130,474,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" box="[1148,1242,474,499]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouali" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1148,1242,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">N. ouali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1254,1348,474,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1254,1348,474,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2016" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mammee" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">N. mammee</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[259,350,510,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[259,350,510,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[367,456,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 − 52. 46 − 48" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1332,1355]" captionTargetBox="[202,1381,199,1308]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[197,1389,193,1312]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 46 − 52. 46 − 48 Neostasina cachote sp. nov., female (46 epigyne, 47 vulva; 48 schematic course of internal duct system); 49 − 52 Neostasina croix sp. nov., male, left palp (49 prolateral, 50 ventral, 51 retrolateral, 52 detail of embolus and TBE). al = anteriad loop of spermathecae; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; mag = anterior groove of median septum; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale lines: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050760/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Figs 50</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[469,513,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 106 − 112" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1806,1829]" captionTargetBox="[220,1370,699,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[211,1376,695,1785]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 106 − 112. Neostasina mammee sp. nov. 86 − 89 Male, left palp (106 prolateral, 107 ventral, 108 retrolateral, 109 detail of embolus and TBE); 110 − 112 Female (110 epigyne, 111 vulva, 112 schematic course of internal duct system). CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; eRTA = extra retrolateral tibial apophysis; FD = fertilization duct; pt = tegular protrusion; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale lines: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050782/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">109</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[526,569,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 123 − 128" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1839,1862]" captionTargetBox="[207,1379,740,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[200,1387,732,1819]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 123 − 128. Neostasina oualie sp. nov. 123 − 125 Male, left palp (123 prolateral, 124 ventral, 125 retrolateral); 126 − 128 Female (126 epigyne, 127 vulva, 128 schematic course of internal duct system). at = anterior twist of spermathecae; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; eRTA = extra retrolateral tibial apophysis; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale lines: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050788/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">124</figureCitation>
) in the TBE bifid, with long and slender branches, the main branch slightly longer than secondary branch (
<figureCitation box="[509,647,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 − 32" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[225,1363,742,1762]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[218,1369,734,1768]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 26 − 32. Neostasina bermudezi sp. nov. 26 − 29 Male, left palp (26 prolateral, 27 ventral, 28 retrolateral, 29 detail of embolus and TBE); 30 − 32 Female (30 epigyne, 31 vulva, 32 schematic course of internal duct system). am = anterior margin of median septum; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; mb = main branch of TBE; pm = posterior margin of median septum; sb = secondary branch of TBE; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale lines: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050754/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Figs 27, 29</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from these species by the embolus distally flattened with a spike-like tip (
<figureCitation box="[500,633,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 − 32" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[225,1363,742,1762]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[218,1369,734,1768]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 26 − 32. Neostasina bermudezi sp. nov. 26 − 29 Male, left palp (26 prolateral, 27 ventral, 28 retrolateral, 29 detail of embolus and TBE); 30 − 32 Female (30 epigyne, 31 vulva, 32 schematic course of internal duct system). am = anterior margin of median septum; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; mb = main branch of TBE; pm = posterior margin of median septum; sb = secondary branch of TBE; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale lines: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050754/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Figs 27, 29</figureCitation>
). Females are distinguished from those of the remaining species of the genus by the anterior rim divided and median septum pentagonal, with lateral margins parallel (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1304,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 − 32" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[225,1363,742,1762]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[218,1369,734,1768]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 26 − 32. Neostasina bermudezi sp. nov. 26 − 29 Male, left palp (26 prolateral, 27 ventral, 28 retrolateral, 29 detail of embolus and TBE); 30 − 32 Female (30 epigyne, 31 vulva, 32 schematic course of internal duct system). am = anterior margin of median septum; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; mb = main branch of TBE; pm = posterior margin of median septum; sb = secondary branch of TBE; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale lines: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050754/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) and by the copulatory ducts almost transversal (
<figureCitation box="[562,645,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 − 32" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[225,1363,742,1762]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[218,1369,734,1768]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 26 − 32. Neostasina bermudezi sp. nov. 26 − 29 Male, left palp (26 prolateral, 27 ventral, 28 retrolateral, 29 detail of embolus and TBE); 30 − 32 Female (30 epigyne, 31 vulva, 32 schematic course of internal duct system). am = anterior margin of median septum; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; mb = main branch of TBE; pm = posterior margin of median septum; sb = secondary branch of TBE; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale lines: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050754/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
